cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving machine translation using neural networks, specifically by encoding the source language with a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. 

The paper also involves deep neural networks, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks implies a focus on image processing, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of gating mechanisms, which are commonly used in recurrent neural networks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
